cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep learning methods applied to computer vision tasks, specifically multimodal image super-resolution. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also incorporates sparse priors, which suggests a possible connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of side information and the development of deep models may also suggest a connection to cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves designing a deep learning architecture, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the iterative algorithm used for sparse approximation may suggest a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
